## 🚀 Installation Guide

### Step 1: Install Go

#### macOS
```bash
# Using Homebrew (recommended)
brew install go

# Or download from official site
# https://go.dev/dl/
Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)
bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install golang-go
Windows
Download installer from: https://go.dev/dl/

Verify installation:

bash
go version
# Should output: go version go1.21.x or higher
Step 2: Install Ollama
macOS
bash
# Using curl (recommended)
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

# Or download the .dmg from https://ollama.com/download
Linux
bash
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
Windows
Download installer from: https://ollama.com/download

Verify Ollama is running:

bash
# Check if Ollama service is active
ollama --version

# Test API endpoint
curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags
Note: On first install, Ollama automatically starts as a background service. You don't need to manually run ollama serve unless you want to see logs.

Step 3: Download AI Model
Choose one model based on your RAM:

Model	Size	RAM Needed	Speed	Quality	Command
llama3.2:3b	2.0 GB	4-6 GB	⚡ Fast	Good	ollama pull llama3.2:3b
phi3:mini	2.5 GB	5-7 GB	⚡ Fast	Good	ollama pull phi3:mini
gemma2:9b	4.0 GB	6-8 GB	🐢 Slower	Better	ollama pull gemma2:9b
mistral:7b	4.0 GB	6-8 GB	🐢 Slower	Better	ollama pull mistral:7b
For Mac with 8GB RAM (like yours), use:

bash
ollama pull llama3.2:3b
Download progress:

bash
# You'll see output like:
# pulling manifest... 
# pulling a80c4f17acd5... 100% ▕████████████████████▏ 2.0 GB
# verifying sha256 digest... 
# success
Verify model is downloaded:

bash
ollama list
# Should show:
# NAME           ID              SIZE      MODIFIED
# llama3.2:3b    a80c4f17acd5    2.0 GB    About a minute ago
Step 4: Clone KanjiForge
