📖 Using KanjiForge
Step 1: Prepare Your Kanji Data
You need to provide kanji data in a text format. Any format works - the AI is smart enough to understand!

Example Data Format 1: Simple
text
駐車 - park
駐車場 - parking lot
駐 - 15 strokes, チュウ
Example Data Format 2: Detailed (like your original data)
text
駐車
park 停车 주차
駐車場ちゅうしゃじょう
a parking lot 停车场 주차장
ちゅうしゃ
駐
15画 チュウ
Example Data Format 3: Minimal
text
駐 (park, チュウ)
無休 (no holiday)
満車 (full parking)
Pro tip: The more data you provide, the better questions the AI will generate!

Step 2: Generate Questions
Paste your kanji data into the textarea on the webpage

Example paste:

text
駐車 - park
駐車場 - parking lot
駐 - 15 strokes, チュウ

無休 - no holiday
無理 - unreasonable
無 - 12 strokes, ム

満車 - full (of cars)
