🔌 API Endpoints
If you want to use KanjiForge programmatically:

POST /api/generate
Generate questions from kanji data.

Request (form-data):

text
kanji_data: 駐車 - park\n駐 - 15画 チュウ
Response:

json
{
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "text": "How to read '駐' in '駐車'?",
      "options": ["A. ちゅう", "B. とまる", "C. つう", "D. しゃ"],
      "correct": "A",
      "explanation": "In '駐車' (parking), '駐' is read as 'ちゅう'."
    }
  ],
  "total": 1
}
POST /api/submit
Submit answers and get score.

Request:

json
{
  "answers": {
    "0": "A",
    "1": "C"
  },
  "questions": [...]
}
Response:

json
{
  "score": 1,
  "total": 2,
  "percentage": 50.0,
  "questions": [...],
  "userAnswers": {"0": "A", "1": "C"}
}
⚙️ Configuration
Change AI Model
Edit handlers/quiz.go, line ~45:

go
"model": "llama3.2:3b",  // Change to "gemma2:9b" or "mistral:7b"
Change Port
Edit main.go, last line:

go
r.Run(":8080")  // Change to ":3000" or any port
Customize Question Style
Edit the buildPrompt() function in handlers/quiz.go:

go
func buildPrompt(kanjiData string) string {
    return fmt.Sprintf(`
Create 3 multiple choice questions for EACH kanji...  // Change 2 to 3 for more questions
Difficulty: N3 level  // Add difficulty level
...
`)
}
🐛 Troubleshooting
Error: "Ollama: address already in use"
Problem: Port 11434 is already occupied.

Solution: This is normal! Ollama is already running in the background. Just use it:

bash
# Verify it's working
ollama list
curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags
Error: "Failed to call AI"
Problem: Cannot connect to Ollama.

Solution: Start Ollama service:

bash
# On macOS/Linux
ollama serve

# On another terminal, verify it's running
curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags
Error: "Model not found"
Problem: The model specified in code isn't downloaded.

Solution: Download the model or change the model name:

bash
# List downloaded models
ollama list

# Download missing model
ollama pull llama3.2:3b

# Or change model in quiz.go to one you have
Slow Question Generation (2+ minutes)
Causes: Large model, low RAM, or other apps using resources.

Solutions:

bash
# Use smaller model
ollama pull llama3.2:3b  # Instead of gemma2:9b

# Close other apps (Chrome, Docker, etc.)

# Check memory pressure on Mac:
# Open Activity Monitor → Memory tab
AI Returns Gibberish or Empty Questions
Problem: Model ran out of memory or prompt too long.

Solutions:

bash
# Restart Ollama
pkill ollama
ollama serve

# Reduce context window (edit quiz.go)
"options": map[string]int{"num_ctx": 2048}  // Add this line
Port 8080 Already in Use
Solution: Change port in main.go:

go
r.Run(":8081")  // Use different port
Then access: http://localhost:8081

💻 System Requirements
Minimum Configuration (Works, but slow)
CPU: 2+ cores

RAM: 4GB

Storage: 10GB

Model: llama3.2:3b

Generation time: 1-2 minutes

Recommended Configuration (Best experience)
CPU: 4+ cores (Apple Silicon M1/M2/M3)

RAM: 8GB+

Storage: 20GB SSD

Model: gemma2:9b or mistral:7b

Generation time: 30-60 seconds

Mac-Specific Notes
Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3): Excellent performance due to unified memory

8GB RAM: Use llama3.2:3b - works perfectly

16GB RAM: Can handle gemma2:9b comfortably

Intel Mac: Still works, but will be slower

